description:
The Old Testament Sanctuary was a symbol of salvation. In the New Testament we see the fulfillment through Jesus Christ. Sin separates us from God. Jesus connects us back to God. Psalm 77:13 says, “Thy way, O God, is in the sanctuary.” In the Old Testament, on the Day of Atonement, the people offered sacrifices and their sins were forgiven. In the same way, when we come to Jesus Christ, our sins are forgiven. In this video, Chad Kreuzer explains the deep connection between the Old Testament Sanctuary and the New Testament fulfilled plan of salvation.
